  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Police Professionalization and Community Policing in Kasai Oriental Province, Democratic Republic of the Congo &#x2013; Phase III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the local authorities&apos; request and based on positive results achieved during the previous project phases, this project aims to expand the community policing methodology into the Dibindi district. At the same time, to consolidate the successes of the previous project phases, the new phase continues to monitor the functioning and activities of security actors of the Bipemba district (Project Phase 1) and the Muya district (Project Phase 2). Based on these monitoring activities, technical and logistical support is provided when needed. IOM also monitors the positive engagement of security actors towards communities.  This support mostly concerns the organization of neighborhood meetings and Local Security Committees (Conseils Locaux pour la S&#xE9;curit&#xE9; de Proximit&#xE9;) meetings. To improve the security of the communities in Dibindi district, the project adopts a holistic approach by targeting all security actors and communities, and by supporting the creation of structures and mechanisms to better manage security in line with the community policing principles.</narrative>
  </description>
